The paper discusses a lightweight approach to encryption and compression, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The use of Asymmetric Numeral Systems for entropy coding is a computational problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of this approach in machine-to-machine communication and the Internet of Things, which is a topic in distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
